  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>School</strong>&nbsp;illusion&nbsp;(glamer);\n    <strong>Level</strong>&nbsp;alchemist 3, antipaladin 3, bard 3, inquisitor 3, medium 3, mesmerist 3, occultist 3, psychic 3, sorcerer/wizard 3, witch 3;\n    \n    \n    \n    \n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Casting Time</strong>&nbsp;1 standard action<br>\n    <strong>Components</strong>&nbsp;V, S<br>\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Range</strong>&nbsp;personal<br>\n    \n    <strong>Targets</strong>&nbsp;you<br>\n    \n    <strong>Duration</strong>&nbsp;10 minutes/level (D)<br>\n    \n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  <p>This spell functions as <i><i>disguise</i> self</i>, except as a swift action you can alter the <i>disguise</i> (within the limitations of <i><i>disguise</i> self</i>). For example, you could make yourself look like a young human city guard, then an old elven wizard of the opposite gender, then a halfling thief, and so on. You can change the <i>disguise</i> a number of times equal to your caster level.</p>\n</div>\n",
